{"config":{"separator":"[\\s\\-_,:!=\\[\\]()\\\\\"`/]+|\\.(?!\\d)"},"items":[{"location":"","level":1,"title":"Documentation","text":"<p>This directory contains the Sphinx documentation for Lock &amp; Key.</p>","path":["Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#building-documentation","level":2,"title":"Building Documentation","text":"<p>To build the documentation:</p> <pre><code># Build documentation\nhatch run dev:docs\n\n# Clean build (rebuild everything)\nhatch run dev:docs-clean\n\n# Serve documentation locally on port 8000\nhatch run dev:docs-serve\n</code></pre>","path":["Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#structure","level":2,"title":"Structure","text":"<ul> <li><code>source/</code> - Documentation source files</li> <li><code>conf.py</code> - Sphinx configuration</li> <li><code>index.rst</code> - Main documentation page</li> <li><code>installation.rst</code> - Installation instructions</li> <li><code>usage.rst</code> - Usage examples and CLI reference</li> <li><code>api.rst</code> - API documentation (auto-generated)</li> <li><code>development.rst</code> - Development and contributing guide</li> <li><code>_static/</code> - Static files (CSS, images, etc.)</li> <li><code>_templates/</code> - Custom Sphinx templates</li> <li><code>build/</code> - Generated HTML documentation (gitignored)</li> </ul>","path":["Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#viewing-documentation","level":2,"title":"Viewing Documentation","text":"<p>After building, open <code>build/index.html</code> in your browser or use the serve command:</p> <pre><code>hatch run dev:docs-serve\n</code></pre> <p>Then visit http://localhost:8000</p>","path":["Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#documentation-format","level":2,"title":"Documentation Format","text":"<p>The documentation uses reStructuredText (.rst) format and supports:</p> <ul> <li>Code blocks with syntax highlighting</li> <li>Cross-references to API documentation  </li> <li>Intersphinx links to Python, boto3, and click documentation</li> <li>MyST parser for Markdown support</li> </ul>","path":["Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#theme","level":2,"title":"Theme","text":"<p>Uses the Furo theme for a modern, clean appearance.</p>","path":["Documentation"],"tags":[]},{"location":"","level":1,"title":"Lock-And-Key","text":"<p>Lock &amp; Key is a comprehensive cloud security scanner that analyzes access policies and resource-based policies across multiple cloud providers to identify security vulnerabilities, excessive permissions, and compliance issues.</p>","path":["Lock-And-Key"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#features","level":2,"title":"Features","text":"<ul> <li>☁️ Multi-Cloud Support: AWS (fully implemented), Azure (in progress), GCP (in progress)</li> <li>🔍 Comprehensive Policy Analysis: Scans IAM policies and resource-based policies across all supported services</li> <li>🛡️ Security Vulnerability Detection: Identifies privilege escalation risks, wildcard permissions, and administrative access</li> <li>💻 Interactive CLI: User-friendly command-line interface with rich formatting and progress indicators</li> <li>📊 Detailed Reporting: Generates JSON reports with actionable findings and recommendations</li> <li>⚖️ Least Privilege Analysis: Highlights violations of the principle of least privilege</li> </ul>","path":["Lock-And-Key"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#quick-start","level":2,"title":"Quick Start","text":"","path":["Lock-And-Key"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#installation","level":3,"title":"Installation","text":"<pre><code># Basic installation\npip install lock-and-key\n\n# With enhanced AWS support (better IDE experience)\npip install lock-and-key[aws]\n\n# For developers (includes testing and linting tools)\npip install lock-and-key[dev]\n\n# Everything included\npip install lock-and-key[all]\n</code></pre>","path":["Lock-And-Key"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#run-your-first-scan","level":3,"title":"Run Your First Scan","text":"<pre><code># Interactive mode (recommended for first-time users)\nlock-and-key interactive\n\n# Direct AWS scan with profile\nlock-and-key scan --provider AWS --profile my-profile\n</code></pre>","path":["Lock-And-Key"],"tags":[]},{"location":"#options","level":3,"title":"Options","text":"<ul> <li><code>--output-dir</code>: Specify output directory for reports (default: <code>./reports</code>)</li> <li><code>--provider</code>: Choose cloud provider (AWS, Azure, GCP)</li> <li>Various credential options for each provider</li> </ul>","path":["Lock-And-Key"],"tags":[]},{"location":"api/cli/","level":1,"title":"Cli","text":"","path":["📚 API Reference","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"api/cli/#lock_and_key.cli","level":2,"title":"<code>lock_and_key.cli</code>","text":"<p>Command-line interface for Lock &amp; Key.</p>","path":["📚 API Reference","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"api/cli/#lock_and_key.cli.cli","level":3,"title":"<code>cli() -&gt; None</code>","text":"<p>Lock &amp; Key Cloud Scanner CLI.</p>","path":["📚 API Reference","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"api/cli/#lock_and_key.cli.interactive","level":3,"title":"<code>interactive(output_dir: str) -&gt; None</code>","text":"<p>Run the interactive cloud scan workflow.</p>","path":["📚 API Reference","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"api/cli/#lock_and_key.cli.scan","level":3,"title":"<code>scan(provider: str, output_dir: str, **kwargs: Any) -&gt; None</code>","text":"<p>Run a single provider scan with provided credentials.</p>","path":["📚 API Reference","Cli"],"tags":[]},{"location":"api/main/","level":1,"title":"Main","text":"","path":["📚 API Reference","Main"],"tags":[]},{"location":"api/main/#lock_and_key.main","level":2,"title":"<code>lock_and_key.main</code>","text":"<p>Entry point for Lock &amp; Key CLI.</p>","path":["📚 API Reference","Main"],"tags":[]},{"location":"api/config/settings/","level":1,"title":"Settings","text":"","path":["📚 API Reference","Config","Settings"],"tags":[]},{"location":"api/config/settings/#lock_and_key.config.settings","level":2,"title":"<code>lock_and_key.co