           # Core functionality\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   ├── scanner.py           # Main scanner class\n│   └── ui.py               # UI utilities\n├── models/                  # Data models\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   ├── credentials.py       # Credential models\n│   └── scan_results.py     # Scan result models\n├── providers/              # Cloud provider implementations\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   ├── base.py             # Base provider interface\n│   ├── aws.py              # AWS provider\n│   ├── gcp.py              # GCP provider\n│   └── azure.py            # Azure provider\n├── config/                 # Configuration management\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   └── settings.py         # Application settings\n├── exceptions/             # Custom exceptions\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   └── base.py             # Base exception classes\n└── modules/                # Legacy analysis modules (to be refactored)\n    └── aws/\n        ├── clients/\n        └── object_classes/\n</code></pre>","path":["Lock &amp; Key Architecture"],"tags":[]},{"location":"architecture/#design-principles","level":2,"title":"Design Principles","text":"<ol> <li>Separation of Concerns: Each module has a single responsibility</li> <li>Dependency Injection: Providers are pluggable and testable</li> <li>Type Safety: Full type hints throughout the codebase</li> <li>Error Handling: Custom exceptions for different error types</li> <li>Extensibility: Easy to add new cloud providers</li> </ol>","path":["Lock &amp; Key Architecture"],"tags":[]},{"location":"architecture/#key-components","level":2,"title":"Key Components","text":"","path":["Lock &amp; Key Architecture"],"tags":[]},{"location":"architecture/#core-scanner-corescannerpy","level":3,"title":"Core Scanner (<code>core/scanner.py</code>)","text":"<ul> <li>Main orchestration logic</li> <li>Handles interactive and programmatic workflows</li> <li>Manages provider selection and credential building</li> </ul>","path":["Lock &amp; Key Architecture"],"tags":[]},{"location":"architecture/#providers-providers","level":3,"title":"Providers (<code>providers/</code>)","text":"<ul> <li>Pluggable cloud provider implementations</li> <li>Each provider implements the same interface</li> <li>Easy to add new providers</li> </ul>","path":["Lock &amp; Key Architecture"],"tags":[]},{"location":"architecture/#models-models","level":3,"title":"Models (<code>models/</code>)","text":"<ul> <li>Pydantic models for data validation</li> <li>Separate credential and result models</li> <li>Type-safe data structures</li> </ul>","path":["Lock &amp; Key Architecture"],"tags":[]},{"location":"architecture/#cli-clipy","level":3,"title":"CLI (<code>cli.py</code>)","text":"<ul> <li>Clean Click-based command interface</li> <li>Interactive and non-interactive modes</li> <li>Proper argument validation</li> </ul>","path":["Lock &amp; Key Architecture"],"tags":[]},{"location":"architecture/#usage","level":2,"title":"Usage","text":"","path":["Lock &amp; Key Architecture"],"tags":[]},{"location":"architecture/#interactive-mode","level":3,"title":"Interactive Mode","text":"<pre><code>lock-and-key interactive\n</code></pre>","path":["Lock &amp; Key Architecture"],"tags":[]},{"location":"architecture/#direct-scan","level":3,"title":"Direct Scan","text":"<pre><code>lock-and-key scan --provider AWS --profile my-profile\n</code></pre>","path":["Lock &amp; Key Architecture"],"tags":[]},{"location":"architecture/#programmatic-usage","level":3,"title":"Programmatic Usage","text":"<pre><code>from lock_and_key import LockAndKeyScanner\n\nscanner = LockAndKeyScanner()\nscanner.run_interactive()\n</code></pre>","path":["Lock &amp; Key Architecture"],"tags":[]}]}